# Domain module rules

Business logic lives here — **not** in route handlers, React components, or API route files.

## Patterns

1. Mutations take an entity number (`rpNum` / `ipNum`) plus the acting user's email where permissions matter; they throw `Error` with a user-facing message on failure (Server Actions map it to `{ error }`).
2. After Prisma writes that must reach the Rep.Parts26 sheet, call `enqueueSheetSync("rp"|"ip", entityId)` from `panel-orders.ts`.
3. Authorization: use `authz.ts` helpers (`getReviewerDashboardConfig`, `isAdminUser`, `isWorkshopNoteViewerForFactory`, …) and `viewer-context.ts` — enforce server-side, not only in UI.
4. Slack / sheet side effects go through `src/lib/integrations/` and must respect automation toggles (`automation-settings.ts`) — fire-and-forget with `.catch`, never block the mutation.
5. Reuse existing modules — search `src/lib/domain/` before adding new files.

## File naming

Verb-noun or entity-concern, one concern per file: `rp-create.ts`, `rp-mutations.ts`, `ip-mutations.ts`, `dashboard-parts.ts`, `factory-fill.ts`.

## When matching legacy behaviour

Search `legacy-gas/WebAppLogic.js` and `legacy-gas/LoggerLogic.js` first, port the behaviour here, and keep edge cases (status strings, sorting, note formats) byte-compatible with the sheet.

